@page "/terms"
@layout PublicLayout

<PageTitle>Terms of Service - grow.IT</PageTitle>

<div class="contact-page footer-info-page">
    <section class="contact-hero">
        <span class="contact-kicker">Terms</span>
        <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
        <p>Last updated: July 4, 2026. These terms describe basic expectations for using Grow.IT and related services.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="contact-form-section">
        <article class="contact-form-card">
            <h2>Use of the platform</h2>
            <p>Grow.IT may be used by authorized users for legitimate organization operations, service tracking, reporting, readiness planning, and related administrative work.</p>

            <h2>Account responsibility</h2>
            <p>Customer organizations are responsible for inviting the right users, assigning roles carefully, protecting credentials, and keeping account and organization information accurate.</p>

            <h2>Data responsibility</h2>
            <p>Organizations are responsible for the accuracy, permission, and lawful use of the data entered into Grow.IT. Customer organizations retain ownership of their submitted operational data.</p>

            <h2>Reports and readiness scores</h2>
            <p>Grow.IT reports and ASC readiness signals are planning tools based on saved data. They do not guarantee funding, loan approval, grant awards, investment, or donor support.</p>

            <h2>Service changes</h2>
            <p>We may update features, pricing, policies, security controls, and terms as the product evolves. Material changes will be communicated through appropriate product or customer channels.</p>
        </article>
    </section>

    <section class="contact-cta">
        <div class="contact-cta-card">
            <h2>Need help reviewing terms?</h2>
            <p>Contact our team for procurement, board, or implementation clarification.</p>
            <div class="contact-cta-actions">
                <a href="/contact?subject=Terms%20Clarification" class="btn btn-primary">Request Clarification</a>
                <a href="/privacy" class="btn btn-outline">Read Privacy Policy</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>
